getBaseModel

public OWLOntologyImpl getBaseModel()
Description copied from interface: OWLModel
Get the model where the changes will be made (create and add) by default. (Note that set and remove methods invoked on this model my cause updates throughout the entire model, i.e., also in sub models of this model.)

If this model is a KB then it is the base ontology of the KB. At the creation time of each KB an empty ontology is created to be the base ontology of the KB. All createXXX and addXXX methods will actually modify this base ontology. However, removeXXX and setXXX methods may modify any sub ontology in the KB, provided that it is not in read-only mode.

If this model is a ontology then the base model is the ontology not containing the statements of its imported ontologies (if any).

Specified by:
getBaseModel in interface OWLModel
Returns:
The base model.

addImport

public void addImport(OWLOntology ontology)
Description copied from interface: OWLOntology
Import the given ontology to this ontology, that is, add all statements (as a sub model) to this model. Note that it wont be imported if (i) it is already imported or (ii) if one of the already imported ontologies (if any) imports the given ontology.

This will cause the associated inference engine (if any) to update, so this may be an expensive operation in some cases.

Specified by:
addImport in interface OWLOntology
Parameters:
ontology - The ontology to import.

addImports

public void addImports(java.util.Collection<OWLOntology> theImports)
Description copied from interface: OWLOntology
Import the given ontologies to this ontology, that is, add all statements (as a sub model) of each ontology to this model. Note that an ontology o in the given collection wont be imported if (i) it is already imported or (ii) if one of the already imported ontologies (if any) imports o. Therefore, the order of the given collection may have an impact on which ontologies will actually be added as imports.

This will cause the associated inference engine (if any) to update, so this may be an expensive operation in some cases.

Specified by:
addImports in interface OWLOntology
Parameters:
theImports - The ontologies to import.

isReadOnly

public boolean isReadOnly()
Description copied from interface: OWLOntology
Check if this ontology is marked to not allow modifications. This property is transitive: imports of a read-only ontology (if any) are also read-only (and vice versa) provided that they were retrieved using OWLOntology.getImports(boolean). However, this property is local regarding the backing KB: While it is reflected for this ontology in the KB, it is not for imports of this ontology. This is due to the fact that a imported ontology may be imported by another ontology as well and we decided not to globalize this property in this case.

Any attempt to modify a read-only ontology via one of the addXXX, createXXX, removeXXX, setXXX methods will result in a UnsupportedOperationException.

Note, however, that when a reasoner gets attached it can, of course, internally add deduced statements.

Specified by:
isReadOnly in interface OWLOntology
Returns:
true if this ontology cannot be modified.
See Also:
OWLOntology.setReadOnly(boolean)

protected void removeAll(Resource s,
                         Property p,

Description copied from class: OWLModelImpl
Implementations need to remove all triples. A value of null for one or more parameter is to be interpreted as the wildcard. For instance, (s, p, null) means to remove *all* objects of the subject s with property p.
